2022-01-19 14:52:20	zicada	inhahe_: im trying to get to why you can't do this
2022-01-19 14:52:44	zicada	inhahe_: i was talking about the breakdown of the wave function. What causes that to happen ? observation. What causes observation ?
2022-01-19 14:52:44	lckdscl	> to say the above is not a logical reduction
2022-01-19 14:53:06	zicada	inhahe_: sufficiently complex systems, cause observation, eg cause the breakdown of the wave function
2022-01-19 14:53:22	zicada	inhahe_: and here's the crux: This is why they cool quantum computers down to as close to 0 kelvin as possible
2022-01-19 14:54:04	zicada	inhahe_: because the closer you get to 0 kelvin, the less quantum effects you get, at 0 kelvin you CAN calculate both the position and the moment of a particle right, but the hotter a system is, the more random it is (entropy)
2022-01-19 14:54:11	inhahe_	consciousness doesn't have to utilize quantum phenomena in the same way that quantum computers do
2022-01-19 14:54:22	zicada	inhahe_: in a quantum computer you dont WANT anything to do any observing, until you are ready
2022-01-19 14:54:38	zicada	you want to control when the breakdown of the wave-function occurs
2022-01-19 14:54:56	inhahe_	maybe just the presence of randomness is enough, because the magic is in the meaning behind the random behaviors
2022-01-19 14:54:57	zicada	do you see now why you can't "scale up" these things ?
2022-01-19 14:55:08	zicada	once you scale up, everything is always observed, because everyting is complex macro systems
2022-01-19 14:55:38	zicada	that in a nutshell is why you cant say "but my brain is controlled with electrons that are quantum therefore my brain is quantum"
2022-01-19 14:55:56	inhahe_	do you deny that quantum random events are always happening even in something other than a quantum computer?
