2022-01-19 16:03:45	sklm	mycroftiv: i think i'm interested in how we find out that a certain system exhibits a mathematical structure, even if we don't construe this system to exhibit this structure - I have a general interest in the question of how mathematics applies to the world/how mathematical structures can be used to represent physical structures, so i find your constructive approach really interesting, but was wondering how to
2022-01-19 16:03:45	sklm	transfer that to a case in which we don't construct the physical system (i.e. in contrast to the construction/realisation of a mathematical structure using a programming language). I hope this makes sense?
2022-01-19 16:04:49	mycroftiv	sklm: sure, well i think the general concepts of isomorphism and measurements and models all fit together for how we translate structures
2022-01-19 16:05:51	sklm	ok, i'm always hesitant to use the concept of isomorphism beyond the comparison of mathematical structures proper. but maybe I'm overly hesitant at this point :)
2022-01-19 16:06:17	mycroftiv	sklm: do you have an example of a specific mathematical structure and/or specific real world scenario, where going back and forth between math<->reality seems notably challenging in your view?
2022-01-19 16:06:49	mycroftiv	sklm: in my view, something like the whole concept of 'counting numbers' is an isomorphism between the abstract structure of the naturals, and how real world solid macro objects work
2022-01-19 16:07:42	Ungwelian	Any kind of space colonization is going to be really hard.
2022-01-19 16:07:47	mycroftiv	i can take 4 apples and demonstrate 2 apples + 2 apples = 4 apples and this structural isomorphism between formal rules and behaviors and reality behavior is what its all about
2022-01-19 16:08:11	Ungwelian	It sounds nice, but space is really inhospitable. And other planets in the solar system are too.
2022-01-19 16:08:58	mycroftiv	ungwelian: yeah its clear all the stuff i read in the 1970s was grossly overoptimistic in its extrapolations. we did sputnik->apollo in 20 years, people thought 20 more was mars and 20 more was full solar system
2022-01-19 16:08:59	zicada	sklm: in my opinion its useful to think about this in terms of models. That all humans have a model of the world in their heads, that is dynamic and gets updated based in input/experience, a models of h
2022-01-19 16:09:24	Ungwelian	mycroftiv, yeah.
2022-01-19 16:09:37	sklm	yeah, I think that this is the standard view. but this depends on a extra-mathematical definition of "isomorphism", and I'm not sure whether I've encountered such a definition (in the debates about scientific representation, for example, people tend to assume, but not define such a concept)
2022-01-19 16:09:47	Ungwelian	Lately they found out that the sand in Mars is toxic.
2022-01-19 16:10:06	mycroftiv	sklm: well its certainly not strictly mathematical, but we can just say 'translation or mapping
2022-01-19 16:11:34	zicada	mycroftiv: its been shown that rats have an internal model of their surroundings that includes several attributes, and it gets updated in realtime whenver new experiences reach a given treshold
2022-01-19 16:11:35	mycroftiv	something like how we go from cosmological observations to using general relativistic spacetime mathematics and why we feel that a mathematical object like the riemann tensor has 'physical meaning' correlated to observations is intricate
2022-01-19 16:11:48	sklm	mycroftiv: even in this case, I would say that 'translation' or 'mapping' are mathematical notions if applied to mathematical structures ;) I think you are correct, though, but I'm sometimes wondering how to make this precise, and think that in the end we have to rely on more or less arbitrary stipulations at some point
2022-01-19 16:11:54	mycroftiv	zicada: yes the idea of mind as model of the universe is kind of fundamental to me
2022-01-19 16:12:20	zicada	mycroftiv: do you have any experience with software development ?
2022-01-19 16:12:48	mycroftiv	sklm: this is an intersting point you are drawing attention to. i admit for myself the whole mapping back and forth between math and reality is incessant and instinctive and im with max tegmark on thinking of reality as 'made of math' somewhat
2022-01-19 16:13:27	mycroftiv	zicada: yes, os level development in plan 9 C and general unix, also agda dependent types, http://harmonicultrafilter.com/m/music-index.html has links to a lot of work
2022-01-19 16:13:27	ro-bot-o	[url] Harmonic Ultrafilter Music | harmonicultrafilter.com
2022-01-19 16:14:13	mycroftiv	computer programming has been one of the major domains i have tried to create tangible applications and translations of mathematical ideas to concrete form
2022-01-19 16:14:33	zicada	mycroftiv: cool
2022-01-19 16:14:44	mycroftiv	although i did not have a view of ultrafilters and large cardinals until the past few years, after finishing most of my plan 9 OS development and deployments
2022-01-19 16:14:59	sklm	mycroftiv: I tend to be cautious about the claim that reality is 'made of math', but this of course would solve the worry
2022-01-19 16:15:42	mycroftiv	sklm: to me its almost vacuous - of course once we have information or data of any kind, it has some kind symbolic/logical representation which can be mathematically understood
2022-01-19 16:16:31	mycroftiv	sklm: so any speech act or mark on paper has this aspect of being tangible information which can then be formally described, so if we think reality is non-mathematical, we cant really use numbers or speech or pictures because those can all be 'digitized'
2022-01-19 16:17:04	mycroftiv	but maybe somehow Ineffable existence is indeed prior to all symbols
2022-01-19 16:17:29	mycroftiv	but we cant capture that understanding in symbols. tao that can be spoken is not the true tao, etc.
2022-01-19 16:18:13	mycroftiv	but even if you feel that attitude, it seems like if you want to do anything in the world, you still make telescopes and numbers and language and operate in the sub-realm of 'that which can be symbolized'
2022-01-19 16:19:06	mycroftiv	and you can still transfer information every which way back and forth between more and less explicit and formalized symbolic and computational and numeric and language information that is all logically analyzable
2022-01-19 16:19:45	sklm	mycroftiv: i see, i think i would end up at a similar point, but stress the point that taking something as information (marks on paper) is basically an additional step of conceptualisation with the choice of using a particular (mathematical) language to express this
2022-01-19 16:20:05	mycroftiv	sklm: i agree with that completely, seems like good language to me
2022-01-19 16:21:31	sklm	maybe I should read tegmark and check whether his claims are compatible with a certain Viennese brand of empiricism
2022-01-19 16:22:10	mycroftiv	sklm: its interesting stuff, it really isnt too much 'claims' just kind of a perspective on math and reality
