2022-01-20 12:24:14	inhahe_	 sentences longer than what, and why couldnt they be longer, and how can you say sentences when there is only one sentence
2022-01-20 12:24:16	I_Am_M00t	if you have the numbers "1,2" and an operator "=", then you get four statements each with 3 words: 1=1, 1=2, 2=1, 2=2. But if i were to remove the meaning from "=", i would instead get four statements each with one word (1=1, 1=2, 2=1, 2=2)
2022-01-20 12:24:28	mycroftiv	atque: in univalent math, you can say things are '=' if you can construct an equivalence function between them, basically a 1-to-1 matching (bijection)
2022-01-20 12:24:33	I_Am_M00t	in the former case "1=1" is 3 words, in the latter case "1=1" is a single word, like "apple"
2022-01-20 12:25:24	inhahe_	I_Am_M00t: i guess that's true, but it's irrelevant because in your language there's only one statement either way
2022-01-20 12:25:26	I_Am_M00t	in the former case "1=1" is broken up into "1", "=", "1", in the latter case it's just a single word
2022-01-20 12:25:26	mycroftiv	atque: so the idea is to capture the idea of identification of isomorphic structures which is common in mathematical practice, even though this will prove some quite different things are equal/can be identified
2022-01-20 12:25:33	I_Am_M00t	it's not irrelevant tho
2022-01-20 12:25:45	I_Am_M00t	because in the evaluation step different things happen
2022-01-20 12:25:53	inhahe_	only one thing can happen
2022-01-20 12:25:58	I_Am_M00t	no, different things happen
2022-01-20 12:26:27	inhahe_	what do you mean by different things
2022-01-20 12:26:28	I_Am_M00t	in the former case "1=1" is calculated, and "1" is correctly mapped to "1"
2022-01-20 12:26:40	I_Am_M00t	in the latter case "1=1" is directly mapped to "true"
2022-01-20 12:26:54	I_Am_M00t	because it's just a word
2022-01-20 12:27:16	inhahe_	but if there can be only one result of the calculation, how you do the calculation is irrelevant
2022-01-20 12:27:22	inhahe_	it's superfluous
2022-01-20 12:27:42	mycroftiv	inhahe_: whether extensional equivalence is used for equality or not is up to the formal system
2022-01-20 12:27:48	I_Am_M00t	well, that's what i was hinting at before... the irrelevant can only be seen if you look at the meta
2022-01-20 12:27:55	I_Am_M00t	within the language itself it's perfectly relevant
2022-01-20 12:28:12	mycroftiv	some systems actually dont have extensional equivalence and the different ways of calculating the same value are not considered equivalent
2022-01-20 12:29:25	mycroftiv	in standard mathematics we do have function extensionality, but we can make our concept of equality intensional instead and say we care about how the outputs are constructed, not just what the outputs are
2022-01-20 12:29:59	inhahe_	mycroftiv: i think if in a language you can only have one possible sentence, it makes no difference how you break up the parts of that sentence and how you say the parts relate to each other, because there can be no different consequences, so each possible way is equally right or wrong, and hence meaningless. what do you say about that?
2022-01-20 12:30:04	I_Am_M00t	inhahe_: either way, i think the problem here lies in the evaluation function itself, in the things that have been unsaid, that are defined as soon as you talk about logic, and the idea of truths and falsehoods. The problem is not with the langauge
