2022-01-20 14:12:09	amigojapan	inhahe_: you mention “the cheese is in my pocket” is true if and only if the cheese is in my pocket. The problem with that formulation is that it’s essentially just a tautology. But I don't believe it is a tautology. The first sentence is a truth statement, and the second statement is a comment of a phisical phenomenon. Namely that there is someone actually holding cheese inside his pocket
2022-01-20 14:12:33	amigojapan	It may sound like a tautology but it is not
2022-01-20 14:13:34	amigojapan	inhahe_: I could say "I am drinking seltzer, and it would be true cause I am, but it w would be false if I was drinking coffee
2022-01-20 14:15:54	amigojapan	inhahe_: so I think a true statement is a description of something that is actually happening. Well there can be true statements about fantasy too but let's not get into that now
2022-01-20 14:16:02	<--	kish` (~aqua@user/aqua) has quit (Remote host closed the connection)
2022-01-20 14:16:27	-->	kish` [aqua] (gpg&age keys: tinyurl.com/kishkey1) (~aqua@user/aqua) has joined ##philosophy
2022-01-20 14:18:06	inhahe_	amigojapan: but i go on to say that the problem is that they're both propositions and reality isn't propositional
2022-01-20 14:20:08	amigojapan	inhahe_: what if you are observing me and I put cheese inside my pocket. And you see that, and then I say "I have cheese in my pocket". Then it would be a true statement that your witnessed
2022-01-20 14:21:34	inhahe_	amigojapan: in your hypothetical, you're giving me a proposition and then repeatingh it
2022-01-20 14:21:58	inhahe_	amigojapan: in reality, whatever the state of affairs is, it's not propositional
2022-01-20 14:22:07	inhahe_	and doesn't have a narrator
2022-01-20 14:22:12	inhahe_	that's omniscient
2022-01-20 14:22:18	amigojapan	No, you would be observing my actions. Not listening to a proposition
2022-01-20 14:22:19	inhahe_	as a hypothetical does
2022-01-20 14:23:10	inhahe_	you're presenting the hypothetical in propositional form
2022-01-20 14:23:13	amigojapan	inhahe_: what if I write "we are chatting", that is a true statement
2022-01-20 14:23:26	amigojapan	This is not hypothetical
2022-01-20 14:24:02	inhahe_	amigojapan: okay, but whatever " we are chatting" corresponds to in objective reality is not propositional, so it's not the fact that "we are chatting"
2022-01-20 14:24:16	inhahe_	"we are chatting" is a proposition
2022-01-20 14:24:37	amigojapan	But both you and me know it's true
2022-01-20 14:24:50	inhahe_	so
2022-01-20 14:25:08	inhahe_	truth does tend to be agreed upond
2022-01-20 14:25:18	inhahe_	doesn't mean correspondence theory of truth makes any sense
2022-01-20 14:25:27	inhahe_	at least as formulated in my essay
2022-01-20 14:25:34	inhahe_	which is how i've seen it
2022-01-20 14:25:39	amigojapan	No it's not an agreement it is obvious cause the truth is based on our actions
2022-01-20 14:26:15	inhahe_	that's why it's in agreement
2022-01-20 14:27:06	inhahe_	but whatever 'our actions' really are, they're not propositional in nature
2022-01-20 14:27:16	amigojapan	Ok inhahe_ I would like to continue this chat tomorrow, going to sleep now
2022-01-20 14:27:19	inhahe_	ok later
2022-01-20 14:27:32	amigojapan	Ty
2022-01-20 14:28:10	mycroftiv	tarski formal model-theoretic definition of truth in logic is nice, as to how to think of truth in reality, i feel like a lot of partially overlapping definitions are inevitable
