2022-01-24 12:46:32	mycroftiv	arryana: im not an 'eat the rich' advocate exactly, but again, i support much more equitable distribution of wealth, and ill explain how i did the real thing in life
2022-01-24 12:47:20	mycroftiv	when my dad died in 2013 i inherited a bit of money - not a lot, but a bit - from him, and some of that i think came from a hotel that his parents ran in the black hills of south dakota, for mt rushmore tourists
2022-01-24 12:47:52	mycroftiv	i think the white settlers genocided the native americans out of that sacred land and mt rushmore is a monument to that and money i inherent that stems from that, i should change the wheel of karma with
2022-01-24 12:48:35	mycroftiv	so i went out into my community of madison wisconsin asking people for ideas for how i could donate the money i inherited from my dad to help less privileged peoples, and i donated a lot, more than i spent on any toys for myself by a large amount i think
2022-01-24 12:49:23	mycroftiv	and i am a low income person who is unemployed and supported by my mom and i survive ok so i feel privileged since im warm and can eat food and play video games, but more than that, ill share
2022-01-24 12:49:51	arryana	i lived in appleton for a while.  back then there was no shortage of hmong who needed help
2022-01-24 12:49:54	mycroftiv	arryana: so i hope i might be an exception to your 'invariably find' rule of your previous experience
2022-01-24 12:50:01	arryana	but i don't believe in karma or any other such religious stuff
2022-01-24 12:50:30	arryana	not really.  you feel that your idea of comfortable is good enough.  you didn't give -all- of it away, did you
2022-01-24 12:50:30	arryana	?
2022-01-24 12:50:34	mycroftiv	arryana: that sounds like a great project, i know some about the history of hmong resettlement here in wisconsin. i have a friend who is hmong who works at my local cafe
2022-01-24 12:50:42	arryana	there's still people who have less than you, aren't there?
2022-01-24 12:50:59	inhahe_	The rich don't just have more money, they're very powerful and corrupt and they buy government legislation and political candidates to the detriment of society. And the things they spend their money on, like yachts and huge houses, are extremely inefficient use of resources and labor.
2022-01-24 12:51:09	mycroftiv	arryana: you didnt say 'give up EVERYTHING' you said 'give up anything'
2022-01-24 12:51:24	arryana	i'm not saying it's a bad thing.  i'm just saying that i don't think it's ever going to be a good idea to set a boundary of what other people should have.
2022-01-24 12:51:42	Thelma	mwsb is a very bad man who spreads lies about people
2022-01-24 12:51:45	<--	Thelma (~Thelma@120.22.162.28) has left ##philosophy
2022-01-24 12:51:47	arryana	you seriously think that's how all rich people live?
2022-01-24 12:51:49	arryana	nt the case.
2022-01-24 12:51:59	arryana	jesus.
2022-01-24 12:52:04	 •	arryana hits the drama alarm
2022-01-24 12:52:04	mycroftiv	if other people are starving and some have more than they can even eat and it is rotting then yea i think there needs to be a boundary on what people can have
2022-01-24 12:53:09	inhahe_	i'm for a universal wage cap
2022-01-24 12:53:11	mycroftiv	seems really clear to me that if your belly is full and you have warehouses of grain so you know you and your family will be fed for the rest of your lives, and someone is starving next to you - yes you need to share
2022-01-24 12:53:25	mycroftiv	and if you dont, people are entitled to take some of your hoard
2022-01-24 12:53:43	mycroftiv	but they should always let you see the error of your ways and let you start sharing voluntarily first
2022-01-24 12:54:27	inhahe_	how would you have a boundary on what people can have and  give them the choice to give it away themselves at the same time?
2022-01-24 12:54:43	mycroftiv	i just explained
2022-01-24 12:54:46	arryana	what -you- see as the error of their ways
2022-01-24 12:54:49	arryana	they don't agree
2022-01-24 12:55:13	mycroftiv	if you have plenty for yourself and your family and lots more, and you do not share with someone who is starving, you are not being cool and nice
2022-01-24 12:55:20	mycroftiv	and if you are asked politely to share
2022-01-24 12:55:41	mycroftiv	and then explained in words of one syllable that it is not cool to sit on a mountain of buttered syruped pancakes while a child starves in front of you
2022-01-24 12:55:54	arryana	that's more idealistic than realistic
2022-01-24 12:56:05	mycroftiv	at some point someone will just take the pancakes and share them and tell you to stop your whining
2022-01-24 12:56:08	arryana	and it assumes that your values are more correct than anyone else's
2022-01-24 12:56:09	arryana	so, no.
2022-01-24 12:56:30	mycroftiv	assuming that sharing food is better than letting people starve if there is enough for everyone is a value i will go with
2022-01-24 12:56:57	mycroftiv	if someone says their 'letting people starve because whats mine is mine' is a better value, im gonna say they are wrong. because my relative model truth isnt 'anything goes'
2022-01-24 12:57:07	arryana	i've fostered three kids over the years, largely at my own expense.  but i chose to do that, and to be compelled to do it would be fucked up
2022-01-24 12:57:18	arryana	there are -always- going to be people starving
2022-01-24 12:57:35	mycroftiv	the mathematics and science on that do not support that claim in my opinion
2022-01-24 12:58:19	mycroftiv	you are making claims that it is mathematically and scientifically impossible to feed more people and still let people do what they want and be happy, even more so than now. i dont think we are locked into such grim possibilities
2022-01-24 12:58:22	inhahe_	eating the rich doesn't mean compelling you to foster children. you're not the rich.
2022-01-24 12:58:24	 •	arryana checks out of the conversation
2022-01-24 12:58:41	mycroftiv	i think sharing food for the whole world is not impossible at all and humans can do it. we do produce enough calories
2022-01-24 12:58:44	!=	Atque is now known as hammond
2022-01-24 12:58:49	arryana	magic mathematical answers to impose your morality on other people is too far for me to want to discuss further
2022-01-24 12:58:55	!=	hammond is now known as Atque
2022-01-24 12:58:58	mycroftiv	people starve more because of political bullshit and wars than because of not enough food
2022-01-24 12:59:31	mycroftiv	imposing my morality of sharing food and not letting people starve is not some crazy evil dream of mine. its what most of the world claims it strives for really.
2022-01-24 13:00:20	mycroftiv	about the least controversial opinion i could really think up, that we can actually get the food we produce to people to eat, its mostly just wars and disruptions and weird logistics and priorities that prevent it, and we already do amazingly overall
